  "text": "About 100 g of tomato wet leaves were acid digested by following the procedure given above and the solution was diluted to 100 mL. This solution was evaporated to reduce the volume to 10 mL for preconcentration of As. Arsenic species i.e. trivalent and pentavalent forms from these vegetable samples were estimated by following the procedure described as above [CITATION_1] .",
